============================================================
POLICY ENGINE REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/governance/policy_engine.py

Implement:

PolicyEngine

Methods:

- evaluate(actor, resource_type, action, payload, context) -> PolicyDecision
- evaluate_agent_action(agent_id, resource_type, action, payload, context) -> PolicyDecision
- explain_decision(decision) -> dict
- list_effective_policies(context) -> list[GovernancePolicy]

Default deny policies:

- deny live trading unless explicitly allowed and Guardian approves
- deny real IoT power action unless explicit confirmation and operator permission
- deny real social posting unless approved content and social config permit
- deny secret export unless admin and typed confirmation
- deny plugin secret access unless reviewed and explicitly granted
- deny cross-tenant data access
- require audit for admin actions
- require dry-run for runbook executor by default

Rules:
- Higher priority policies override lower priority policies.
- Explicit deny overrides allow.
- `require_approval` must not auto-approve.
- `dry_run_only` must force dry-run even if caller requested live mode.
- Missing policy store must fail closed if POLICY_FAIL_CLOSED=true.

============================================================
SAFETY ENFORCER REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/governance/safety_enforcer.py

Implement:

SafetyEnforcer

Methods:

- enforce_trading_action(payload, context)
- enforce_iot_action(payload, context)
- enforce_social_action(payload, context)
- enforce_export_action(payload, context)
- enforce_plugin_action(payload, context)
- enforce_worker_task(payload, context)

Each method must return PolicyDecision.

Rules:
- Never bypass Risk Guardian.
- Never bypass content approval.
- Never bypass tenant isolation.
- Never allow unsafe live action by default.
- Every blocked action must emit event and audit log.

